Homeless Period project is encouraging people to donate tampons and towels to homeless shelters . 
  The project was started by Oliver Frost, Josie Shedden and Sara Bakhaty  . 
  Women living on the streets don't have access to proper sanitary care during their periods . 
  There is currently no government funding for sanitary products . 
  A campaign video tells the story of a woman who lived rough in Brixton for six months . 
 